Text.Value: I'll look forward to questioning him, once he comes round. He certainly had plenty to say earlier.
If it had been the dwarf alone, we might have stood a chance, but these doppelgangers... they swarmed us.
A rising star, you say?
Figaro...
A word of advice, then, if I may.
I tried to explain all this to my superiors, but they wouldn't have any of it.
You're not wrong there. Never thought I'd have my life saved by a civilian - thank you.
You're a terrible liar. You've got something. Give it here.
Try to convince my superiors to put some resources into this matter.
You're a terrible liar. Tell me everything - now.
Father has shown me visions - the Temple of Bhaal lurks somewhere in the city.
I've been investigating the recent spate of murders across the city.
Meet me at Basilisk Gate if you've anything more to report. And good luck.
And it's taking place beneath 'Candulhallow's Tombstones'.
I think it may be another Bhaalspawn...
A century ago, there was a child of the god of murder - Sarevok Anchev.
Now if you don't mind, I've an autopsy to request, and a family to inform.
Most of what I know is based on reading into Sarevok's history. I'm sure it's nothing next to your personal experience, but I'll share what I have.
Believe me, I wish I could. But I need this job.
Tell her about the murder target list you found.
I can't keep running from Bhaal forever - I must sever his hold, once and for all.
You should raise this with your superiors, immediately.

EditorData.logicalname: DOESNT KNOW DEVELLA TRIED TO ESCALATE

Text.Value: I gravely hope you mean to dismantle it, and this friendship won't end with crossed swords.
No doubt you found a trail of bodies in their wake?
The Bhaal cult is back, and someone is out there, continuing Sarevok's work.
Awful. I'm sure you've a lot of paperwork to do. I'll leave you to it.
For most, that was the end of it. But cults like that don't disappear overnight.
Tell her of the target list. Say nothing of your intentions.
How did you...? Perhaps it's best I don't ask. Do what you have to do.
Abhorrent?
Wait! I think you'll want to hear what I have to say.
The ritualistic brutality of them... it's extraordinary. And it could only be the work of a Bhaalist.
It's my job to be. Though I confess it has been very interesting.
After what's happened here, they might finally take this seriously. Might.
Gods... This is it. The proof that I was right!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Devella takes and studies the murder target list.

Text.Value: It won't be easy, but I'm glad to hear your conviction.
There's a reverence to these murders, a certain flair. It's as if they were done in worship.
I don't know what will happen to the Gate if you don't, but I do know that you're damn well the best hope we have.
It's not a place I'd ever heard of, if I'm honest. But rumour has it there were some hidden cellars somewhere near the Elfsong.
As if I didn't have enough reason to thank you already.
I'm going to stop my Father, whatever it takes.
These killings aren't random. In fact, they seem to be part of some sort of test.
You need to put a stop to this.
Terrifying?
Stranger things have come back to haunt this city.
I should arrest you at once, but - well, the Bhaalspawn crisis, it's the most interesting criminal plight in Baldurian history.
You're brave, spawn, to put yourself into the heart of the Hells like that. Braver than us all.
Meet me there if you have a change of heart.
I'll take a look into it.
I can't believe I'm glad to see a Bhaalspawn, but gods, I knew you'd be the one to stop this.
Like I said before, it's not something I can look into in an official capacity, but you...
Show her the target list. Say nothing of your intentions.
It's not every day you have the chance to catch a killer in action. Not even in this profession.
Sounds like you have a lot to follow up on. I'll leave you to it.
If it were up to me, I'd have every Fist in the city on this.
I am here to sacrifice you, I'm afraid.
I'm one of the killers trying to become an Unholy Assassin.
The vacuum has already been filled - I am Bhaal's new Chosen.
My best guess says it's whoever runs the tribunal - a Bhaalist ritual of initiation. It's all Dolor could talk about.
You're not going to join me?
Devella Fountainhead. Constable of the Flaming Fist.
Perhaps you will keep your life if you stay away. If you think you can run from Bhaal, I won't blame you.
I have a hand - I plan to infiltrate the tribunal and tear it down from within.
Those doppelgangers are tracking his progress. Apparently this one's a rising star among Bhaalists.
Oh! Oh my. By Ilmater's rack, that's... that's...
If what you claim is true, you wouldn't be helping me here unless you were trying to end Bhaal's hold over you.
I should've known it would be you. Thank you.
It grants them access to a 'tribunal'. From what I could gather, it's some sort of rite of initiation for aspiring cultists to prove their worth.
Don't you think I've tried? They won't listen.
I think they will want to make me leader of their cult very soon.
You - what?! GUARDS!
Leave.
Then there's more of these nutters running around... I thought as much.
I'm glad you're on the right side of this, Bhaalspawn. You could be invaluable, if you can get on the inside.
We were paralysed before we even had the chance to fight back.
The killers paralyse their victims, take their hands as an offering for Bhaal, and make it look like the cult of the Absolute was behind it all.
You have to try to find it and stop the cult. Not for me. For the Baldurians.
Infiltrate the cult. Deceive your Father's lackeys. If Bhaal believes he has you, they will let down their guard.
I don't know where 'Candulhallow's Tombstones' is.
I must find a hand, so I can infiltrate the tribunal and tear it down from within.
Gods save us all if you're right, but I'd believe it. Whoever it is, they are intimately familiar with Sarevok's work.
But you - you're not bound by such constraints. Help me out, here. Help the city out.
So it's all happening again... just like in Sarevok's time...
There's bound to be one moment where he trips up, and you see a way to stand against him.
But you're just one sword against a god - are you sure you're up to it?
Hells, you might be the only one who can stop this. What else do you know?
I killed Bhaal's Chosen, Orin.
Didn't manage to catch him alive, unfortunately, but I did overhear quite a lot of what he had to say.
When I'm done, I'll stop by Basilisk Gate. If you've anything to tell of your investigations by then, I'd love to hear it.
Then I hope you can at least protect yourself, and pray this plot fails.
I killed Bhaal's second favourite child, Orin.
We can question the assailant later, once he comes round, but I think I have it now.
A century ago, Bhaal bred dozens just like you. One of whom was Sarevok Anchev.
What makes you think it's not Sarevok himself?
This is excellent news. Though - perhaps not as excellent as you might imagine.
I'm planning to infiltrate the cult, but I don't know where to start.
You said Sarevok led the cultists a century ago - he can't still be alive, can he?
So this is Bhaal's cruelty... I underestimated it.
He ruled the Iron Throne - a dark tower hiding a darker secret. It was the front for a deadly arms-dealing network.
I wish the Fist could do more. You're useless.
Can't you help me?
Oh believe me, I would love to. If it wouldn't get me fired.
Thank you for believing in me.
I've not ruled out the possibility that it is Sarevok himself.
I know that the murders are connected to Bhaal, if that's what you overheard.
I'll tell you what I know.
When I see you there, Devella, this will all be over.
The brutality of the killings is on a par with Sarevok's own. But there's something more here, something new...
You do? How?
I'll do my best.
If I had a coin for every time a civilian threatened me...

EditorData.NodeContext: weary - she's seen this shit before

Text.Value: Just like the wayward Bhaalspawn who saved the Gate before...
Ah, hells. I will live to warn the Gate. FISTS!
I deserve that one. Detective-in-distress, and all. But I will keep trying.
All right, fine.
See you around, Bhaalspawn. Stay alive for me, won't you?
I'm just a civilian. Forget I said anything.
I've got better things to do than investigate a cult.
You're better off not raising any suspicions. Trust me.
They told me to drop it. Told me the city doesn't need another conspiracy theorist and to get back to doing my job before they find someone else to do it for me.
What will you do in the meantime?
Now if you don't mind, I need to draft a report to my superiors before I forget it all. But don't worry, I'll be sure to put in a good word for you.
And I'll pick up where I left off - the Upper City.
'Candulhallow's Tombstones' - any idea where that is?
*Begrudgingly, you tell her about the murder target list you found.*
You've had a busy tenday. I can't even imagine. Here's what I know.
I'm staying away from Bhaal. I never wanted any part in this.
It's fascinating!
Unlikely?
I am working against Bhaal - I got a hold of the list of murder targets.
I've done everything I can within the remit of my job. Any more, and they'll fire me.
You're not wrong about the cult. I found some Bhaalists in the sewers.
And Figaro... I'll let the family know.
You see, when one cult leader is ousted, all that does is leave a vacuum for the next one to step in.
But you've been investigating too, if I'm not mistaken? You're trying to stop your own kind?
The dwarf mentioned somewhere called 'Candulhallow's Tombstones'. But I can't even look into it... not without getting fired.
I don't know much. I only just found out I was a Bhaalspawn in a vision.
You tell me what you know, and I'll tell you what I know.
The precision of the cuts, the depth, the execution - the best butchers in Faerûn couldn't make a cut like that. Trust me, I've asked them.
That document you showed me before - the one with the victims' names on it - that was the briefing.
I'll bet if you follow the trail of these murders, you'll be able to unearth the truth of this resurgence.
You really are a godsend.
Let me guess - you want me to investigate.
I am in command. Even Bhaal will bow to me eventually.
I'd love to. To be among the minds of the madmen first-hand... But there's not a chance I'd pass.
Good thing indeed.
Bhaal is trying to force me to be his Chosen. I'm doing all I can to resist him.
Not only is the cult back, it's spreading fast. I ran into some Bhaalists in the park.
And I'm glad you're fighting the fight to keep the Dread Lord out of the city.
Then perhaps it's a good job I ran into him.
Weren't you supposed to be protecting patriars in the Upper City?
Where can I find this tribunal?
Then I must doubly warn the patriars if he is soon to lash out at them. I'll be in Basilisk Gate if ever you need.
No idea, unfortunately. But whoever it is, they are intimately familiar with Sarevok's work.
Shame. I really thought you might... have something. But you're right, civilians shouldn't be involved in crime scenes.
I would look into it myself... if it wouldn't get me fired.
Tell me what you heard or the next murder victim will be you.
So the Bhaalists had a new leader, and you killed them...
Now your turn. What do you know about the killings?
I think it may be a Bhaalspawn...
Though you did save my life. So - thanks.
I'm not sure I can be free, but I will do what's right until the end.
Fortunately, the Temple was destroyed, and to cleanse the city of Sarevok's memory, the Iron Throne was torn from its foundations and cast into the Chionthar.
There, he amassed an army, seeking to become a god himself. Under his stewardship, the Bhaal Temple was revived, and with it, the Bhaal cult itself.
Show her the murder target list.
There's no way in the hells that those scenes and these murders aren't connected somehow.
I suppose it was quite an ask... I'll see if I can drum up some support from Basilisk Gate.
I'm working against Bhaal - I found the murderer's target list.
You see, I already reported this to my superiors, but they wouldn't have any of it.
Gods - that's it! Proof that I was right.
I don't know who you are, but I'm glad you were there.
I was on my way to the Upper City when I heard a commotion. I stepped in to see if I could help.
The brutality of the killings is certainly reminiscent of his work. But there's something more here, something new...
The assailant is dead now. But I overheard some of his plans.
You're lucky you met me - most of the Fist wouldn't have believed you were a Bhaalspawn. Think it's Baldurian superstition.
I will, but I'm still obliged to protect the Upper City patriars first.
I suppose I'd better go and find a hand, then.
They're always the same - victim paralysed by poison, Absolutist symbol scrawled on the floor in blood. Hand removed pre-mortem.
Unfortunate?
For most, that was the end of it. But cults like that don't disappear overnight. This list you brought me confirms I'm right.
You see, these murders have been cropping up all over the city. I've been following their trail for a while now, and tracing it back to its roots.
Half the silkroot-chewers in the Gate have claimed to be a Bhaalspawn at one point. The Fist don't listen to ghost stories.
If anyone can, it will be you. Or at least that's what the legends say.
You've seen those gruesome dioramas that have been springing up, right? Corpses posed like unholy paintings, blood everywhere...
Technically, I haven't yet done an inventory of this crime scene, so if something were to go 'missing' from a corpse...

EditorData.NodeContext: suggestive - she's implying you should loot the corpse of the murderer

Text.Value: I'm glad I could keep you safe.
The dwarf mentioned somewhere called 'Candulhallow's Tombstones'.
I was heading that way after we last spoke, when I heard a commotion. I stepped in to see what was going on.
Good thing I was here to save you, then.
You're very excited about Bhaal for someone who's supposed to be protecting the city.
I'm trying to hide from my Father's wrath. I fear what will happen if I delve too deeply.
I'm sorry, who are you?
Perhaps they've even asked you to undertake this gruesome sacrament.
I've been working on an assignment, see - a research project of sorts. I knew my conclusions were sound, but this... I never expected this.
I was hoping you could tell me more.
Follow the trail of these murders. Prove the truth. Use your lineage to get places the Fist can't.
Don't panic, but I'm sort of... his son.
Don't panic, but I'm sort of... his daughter.
Don't panic, but I'm sort of... his spawn.
You are here to help me, and not to sacrifice me, aren't you?
In the meantime, I'm going to Basilisk Gate. I'll try to drum up some support - and warn as many important people as possible. Hope I can yell loud enough.
I really don't know if I'm up to it...
It offers access to the 'tribunal'. An initiation rite, held by your Father's acolytes, that brings a new cultist into the fold.
I have a hand. I'll investigate this tribunal.
You, on the other hand, you've probably seen your fair share of murders since you discovered your heritage.
Listen, I'm grateful that you saved my life. But you really shouldn't have had to. It's my job to keep you safe, not the other way around. Now if you don't mind, I'd like to get back to it.
Tell me what you know. You owe me - I just saved your life.
I wasn't going to let Dolor kill you. Your life is mine.
Any idea who it is?
There's no way in the hells that those scenes and these murders aren't connected, and I think I know what the connection is.

Synopsis: Dialog with Devella when you save her from Dolor at Figaro's.
